The Nautilus DevOps team is gearing up to deploy applications on a Kubernetes cluster 
for migration purposes. A team member has been tasked with creating a ReplicaSet 
outlined below:

Create a ReplicaSet using nginx image with latest tag 
(ensure to specify as nginx:latest) and name it nginx-replicaset.

Apply labels: app as nginx_app, type as front-end.

Name the container nginx-container. Ensure the replica count is 4.

Note: The kubectl utility on the jump-host has been configured to work with the 
Kubernetes cluster.